The paper deals with motion planning for multiple agents, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Gaussian processes and probabilistic inference suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The optimization aspect of the problem falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY), while the multi-agent aspect suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
